    "causal_summary": "The mk-spec-memory and mkcodeindex MCP daemons fail repeatedly during sessions: a missing `/tmp` socket dir crashes startup, the embedding model RSS grows until the OS OOM-kills the process, nothing auto-restarts a dead daemon, reconnects bridge to a dead socket, and rebuilding the server wipes the live `dist/` out from under it",
